column10:
There will be two separate reviews for the original game and Liberation!

Assassin's Creed 3 REMASTERED:
[h1] Pros: [/h1]
- storyline intertwined with real events of the American Revolution;
- very rich open world;
- unrealistically emotional sea battles;
- more varied combat animations;
- different types of opponents;
- a huge range of weapons and used items;
- larger number of side quests (an alternative to Villa Monteriggioni in the 2nd part);
- interesting DLC with 3 unique skills.

[h1] Cons: [/h1]
- simplified battle combats;
- [i] annoying bow disappearance bug*[/i];
- too short subtitle length (as for me it was better in the 2nd part);
- incorrect display of your mark on the map (distance & direction).

*Bug with bow - disappearance is possible only during a fight, when it is not hidden.
FIXING - can't be fixed at all (only start new game from very beginning).
[hr][/hr]Assassin's Creed Liberation HD REMASTERED:
[h1] Pros: [/h1]
- interesting swamp map;
- for the first time you can play as a woman :)
- cool animations during the combat;
- different types of opponents;
- a huge range of weapons and used items.

[h1] Cons: [/h1]
- extremely simple and not memorable storyline;
- [i] annoying voice acting disappearance bug *[/i];
- blurred graphics compared to Assassin's Creed 3.
- extremely inconvenient and too small clearance of the map;
- NO fast travel points.

*Bug with voice acting - after EACH exit from the game voice acting option becomes "undefined" and it's completely unchanged.
FIXING - only by deleting file "OPTIONS" in PC - C:\Users\username\Documents\Assassin's Creed Liberation HD\SAVES

[i] the review is based on the playing from the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/id/jvst_vitalik/recommended/33230/] previous part [/url] [/i]

I got this game (contains Liberation Remastered) for free with AC Odyssey Gold Edition. 

AC III (only focus on main missions and main objects, finished, 17 hours, 38% completion)
story: 6.0/10 (kinda okay)
graphic: 5.0/10 ("remaster" more like HD; little bit dark;)
combat: 4.0/10 (pretty easy, but indicator didn't show even enemy is attacking sometimes)
soundtrack: 5.0/10
game play: 2.5/10
(
 initial key binding for PC is mess; 
 some optional object could be hard and annoying; 
 parkour part can be pretty glitchy;
 switching weapons and tools is wanky;
 traveling through maps is painful that fast travel didn't really help;
 many invisible walls;
 NPC stuck at suspicious state or stuck in place;
 map is designed for console because mouse just didn't work when center isn't there;
 it makes game play so blind and frustration that real life mode didn't contain UI;
 can't interact because of not anonymous;
)
over all: 4.0/10 (this remaster done so little to improve quality of life; only get this game with Odyssey instead of pay alone)


AC III: The Tyranny of King Washington (focus on main missions and main objectives, finished, 4 hours, 61% completion)
episode 1: 4.0/10 (fast travel to mission location is good; but confusion missions and some literally impossible optional objectives are frustrating;)
episode 2: 3.5/10 (switch special powers just like switch tools is painful; more boring and annoying chase sequences; enemies didn't show on mini-map sometimes;)
episode 3: 3.5/10 (grinding side activities to progress main objective; )
over all: 3.5/10 (I'm just glad that I finished the story; dlc is not fun at all)


AC Liberation (focus on main missions, finished, 10 hours, 100% completion)
story: 5/10
graphic: 4/10 (it doesn't look like remastered or HD)
combat: 5/10 (press E but same as AC III, it can be glicthy)
soundtrack: 6/10
game play: 5/10
(
 game provides 3 guises;
 objectives are pretty clear and easy compare to AC III;
 parkour part is great most of time;
 BUT no fast travel so I spend more time on travel than doing mission itself;
 3 guises are really limited in missions;
 path is blocked by bush;
 no damage challenge can be difficult;
)
over all: 5.2/10 (not bad)

How do you manage to make a remaster look and play worse than its original???

It's ugly to look at;
Character models look like clay or plastic Barbie dolls;
Character model eyes are detached and soulless in almost every scene;
The Ubisoft Club outfit fittings for Connor is horrendously out of proportion with his head either looking twice the size of his body or in some scenes the outfit completely affects the face animations and makes his face look like its glowing;
Some Club items still do not appear in game even after reset (have not attempted re installation);
Some cut-scenes are broken, where it is like you got hit with a flashbang just as it started and it does not go away until you exit to main menu and return to the game;
The game is even buggier than the original! How can you make a remaster that is in worse shape than the original??? You just had to make the game actually look good and you could barely even do that!; 
Assassinations from bushes are bugged to where Connor either no longer blends whilst crouched or just refuses TO crouch in order to blend;
Enemy pursuits are broken with random enemy NPC pop-ins around every corner essentially making it much more of a pain and hassle to reduce notoriety;
Missions bug out frequently with kill targets, followings or tailings not being tracked properly or accurately displayed;
Random de-synchronisations after fast travelling to a mission location and stepping a few feet away from the location you spawned at;
Counter indicators tend to not show, counter actions are randomly cancelled out meaning you still get hit after pressing the button, and chain kill attacks are bugged where it stops Connor mid animation;
Performing too many dynamic actions like sprinting, attacking and twirling weapons causes Connor's arms to become straight and stiff to where it looks like he is just using the power of his mind to defeat enemies;
At the Battle of Moulton Hill there is no greater demonstration of awful remastered graphics than here, with the 'gruesome' scenes ending up looking hilarious rather than SOMEWHAT brutal. A soldiers blown off legs look like low poly bread sticks dipped in comical ketchup and another soldier's 'burnt face' just looking like the guy tripped and fell into mud or brown shoe polisher which just made him very very shiny.

I have played the original since its release back in 2012 on the PS3 and have beaten the game at the most, 3 times. I enjoy the story and the combat has always been fun. But this opinion stays true to the original. This so called 'remaster' has caused me more f&*$£@g brain trauma from the sheer overwhelming issues than if I were tackled by Shaq whilst he was wearing Spartan armour. 

Do. Not. Buy. This. Unless you got cash to burn because it is on a very high sale, just use the money to buy the original game and then mod it or something. I got the AC Odyssey Ultimate Edition, thus receiving this for free thinking it was a pretty good deal, but now having played and tried it? This is just depressing to play even at just 10 hours...
